  "description": [
    "IJf Vol 4 No 8 Lincoln 3 Nebraska Official and Legal Newspaper Thursday December 15 1949 SAC Elects Sorensen To Presidency At its regular monthly meeting at the Methodist student house on December 5 the Lincodn So cial Action council held its semi annual election of officers Named to the presidency was Theodore t Ted Sorensen law student and charter member of the council During the coming semiannum he will have the job of directing the coordination of the member organizations programs for then greatest effect He succeeds Wil lard Gaeddert a University of Nebraska physicist as head of the council Mr Sorensen is well known lo cally for his ability as a modera tor having served in that ca pacity a number of times during his student days Last year he chaired both the model UNESCO project at the university and the student Constitutional assembly But more especially he is known to those who know the council for his continuing interest and hard work in the interest of Fair Employment Practices legislation for Nebraska which he carried on as chairman of that committee in the SAC As a student he has been outstanding as a speaker and as a"
  ],
